### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:


This command allows you to connect remotely into an EC2 instance using SSH and forward the local port 5900 (VNC) on your machine to a remote VNC server running inside of that instance over TCP/IP at port number 25900. The "-i" option specifies which private key file should be used for authentication, in this case "~/UserKey.pem". If you don't have such an SSH key pair yet or need help creating one, Google is your friend!
